                                        3168
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " every hour for seven days consecutively on two samples, banana and soap (reference sample) to investigate the aging effect, as described in Section II- A. Furthermore, in this section, the response of the system to the presence and absence of the fruit is studied over four days of measurement on three bananas, to fully investigate the temperature effect. Here, the same samples were also employed to investigate the effect of the fruit mass loss on the recorded "
